  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In addition to the common node clustering and node sampling methods, there is also some innovative graph pooling technologies in the hierarchical graph pooling method.",
    "EdgePool (Diehl 2019) is a pooling method based on edge contraction that reduces the size of the graph by intelligently selecting and merging edges in the graph.",
    "This approach preserves key structure information in the graph while reducing computational complexity.",
    "HaarPooling (Wang et al. 2020a) is a graph pooling technology based on compressed Haar transform.",
    "It first groups the nodes in the graph through a clustering algorithm and then uses the Haar transform to map and aggregate the features of each group of nodes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "EdgePool (Diehl 2019) is a pooling method based on edge contraction that reduces the size of the graph by intelligently selecting and merging edges in the graph.",
    "HaarPooling (Wang et al. 2020a) is a graph pooling technology based on compressed Haar transform."
